<paragraph id="92EFD45ED4EE4D7F15B3B7FC54BB8F27" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
Only one protochestiid amphipod had been previously reported from Thailand. 
<bibRefCitation id="EA48F519E34E00C4FD89FCB016279566" author="Bussarawich, S" journalOrPublisher=") Fifth Seminar on Mangrove Ecosystems, Phuket, Thailand" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" refId="B4" refString="Bussarawich, S, 1985. Amphipod Mangroves Thailand. In: NRCT (Ed.) Fifth Seminar on Mangrove Ecosystems, Phuket, Thailand" title="Amphipod Mangroves Thailand. In: NRCT (Ed." year="1985">Bussarawich (1985)</bibRefCitation>
studied the diversity of amphipods in the mangrove forest and reported 
<taxonomicName id="C263FFEC6F68C09860C09C61EB44C94E" genus="Microchestia" lsidName="Microchestia" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B506C40E01C1202AF5E2C59A6076D72D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Microchestia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp., a member of the family 
<taxonomicName id="F6360D841AE460FAB5D95D48BE810DA5" authorityName="Myers &amp; Lowry" authorityYear="2020" class="Malacostraca" family="Protorchestiidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Amphipoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Protorchestiidae</taxonomicName>
. Later, 
<bibRefCitation id="27C0A72319771F840E9B738B84271E44" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3985.2.1" author="Lowry, JK" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" pagination="151 - 202" refId="B9" refString="Lowry, JK, Springthorpe, RT, 2015. Coastal Talitridae (Amphipoda: Talitroidea) from north-western Australia to Darwin with a revision of the genus Cochinorchestia Lowry &amp; Peart, 2010. Zootaxa 3985 (2): 151 - 202, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3985.2.1" title="Coastal Talitridae (Amphipoda: Talitroidea) from north-western Australia to Darwin with a revision of the genus Cochinorchestia Lowry &amp; Peart, 2010." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3985.2.1" volume="3985" year="2015">Lowry and Springthorpe (2015)</bibRefCitation>
revised the genus 
<taxonomicName id="8C130D3999D9C2775743E3B3EBF147C8" authorityName="Lowry &amp; Peart" authorityYear="2010" class="Malacostraca" family="Protorchestiidae" genus="Cochinorchestia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cochinorchestia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="635925A9AC2DBE4E0CD0272EEF9FAFA4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Cochinorchestia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Lowry &amp; Peart, 2010. Although the 
<taxonomicName id="2FE1FDEBD268E013DD9A2A0A74CB0AD0" authorityName="Bousfield" authorityYear="1984" class="Malacostraca" family="Protorchestiidae" genus="Microrchestia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Microrchestia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="54184C7E79073FD273D725D2A42BAA64" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Microrchestia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. from Thailand was also mentioned as a 
<taxonomicName id="8B4381122C21462B15142E18BE954D12" authorityName="Lowry &amp; Peart" authorityYear="2010" class="Malacostraca" family="Protorchestiidae" genus="Cochinorchestia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cochinorchestia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="918B6E147A7A92DBE37357F98C81CC6B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Cochinorchestia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. based on the illustration of the previous publication, some details such as the maxilliped and gnathopods 1 and 2 remain unclear. The specimens from the report of 
<bibRefCitation id="9B7D2656159AA3E11F3E39010E490A14" author="Bussarawich, S" journalOrPublisher=") Fifth Seminar on Mangrove Ecosystems, Phuket, Thailand" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" refId="B4" refString="Bussarawich, S, 1985. Amphipod Mangroves Thailand. In: NRCT (Ed.) Fifth Seminar on Mangrove Ecosystems, Phuket, Thailand" title="Amphipod Mangroves Thailand. In: NRCT (Ed." year="1985">Bussarawich (1985)</bibRefCitation>
presumed lost, which makes the 
<taxonomicName id="23A93281A0EA66A4404B0704EBCEC665" authorityName="Lowry &amp; Peart" authorityYear="2010" class="Malacostraca" family="Protorchestiidae" genus="Cochinorchestia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cochinorchestia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="44A9E2DE473A6AD7C999E8F7221B12D6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Cochinorchestia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. in this report still tentative.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="243AE440F87172C87B8ACDB2076CC5C6" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
The new genus is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="77BF17F0E4A707FD5BEB35095F098C8D" authorityName="Lowry &amp; Peart" authorityYear="2010" class="Malacostraca" family="Protorchestiidae" genus="Cochinorchestia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cochinorchestia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B8908195663DFD7BF618118DEFE714E7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Cochinorchestia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from China in having: 1) left mandible larcinia mobilis 4-dentate; 2) carpus of pereopod 3 longer than that of pereopod 4; and 3) uropod 1 outer ramus with marginal setae. However, the current genus differs from 
<taxonomicName id="DE26A705B74465C787B2D9D49FCAC422" authorityName="Lowry &amp; Peart" authorityYear="2010" class="Malacostraca" family="Protorchestiidae" genus="Cochinorchestia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cochinorchestia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D839CC5E2CCC476B6A9A47F1196C7531" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Cochinorchestia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having: 1) pereopod 7 without a posterodistal lobe (vs. pereopod 7 with a posterodistal lobe); 2) uropod 1 outer ramus linear (vs. spoon-shaped) and uropod 3 peduncle with 2 robust setae (vs. with 3 robust setae); and 3) uropod 2 outer ramus without robust setae (vs. with marginal robust setae in 1 row).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C85BFF9F7AF879AC1A32EFF551F4947C" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
The new genus is identifiable using the following key to genera of 
<taxonomicName id="DAB68F8E1A46615CF8CC70012AC2956F" authorityName="Myers &amp; Lowry" authorityYear="2020" class="Malacostraca" family="Protorchestiidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Amphipoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Protorchestiidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
